Every year terrible shit happens to queer people that reminds me how important today is. So talk nonstop about being gay or trans or bi because you earned it living in a world that tries everyday to silence you with violence, legislation, and intimidation. Be annoying with it!

And there’s no age limit to this. You can be 50 and not yet realize your sexual or gender identity or maybe you do know and have known a long time but kept it to yourself. It’s never too late to start that process and explore who you are.

The process is different for everyone and there are varying degrees to which you are out and that’s fine. Sometimes it’s for safety but also it’s no one else’s damn business. You choose who to disclose the information to and how.

The concept becomes more and more confusing to me each year. What constitutes being out? When your parents know? When your extended fam knows? When coworkers/classmates know? When the delivery guy who dropped the third dragon dildo on your door this month knows? Who’s to say?
